---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Nous Ergon" description="Nous Ergon is an experimentation harness for systematic equity strategies. Built by Brian McMahon.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-12">
    <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Nous Ergon</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-8">
      &nu;&omicron;&upsilon;&sigmaf; &epsilon;&rho;&gamma;&omicron;&nu; &mdash; <em>intelligence at work</em>
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">Thesis</h2>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Build an experimentation harness for systematic equity strategies &mdash;
      multi-agent research, machine-learning prediction, risk-gated execution,
      weekly self-tuning &mdash; and instrument every decision it makes end-to-end.
      The orchestration pattern consists of six modules collaborating through
      S3 contracts, three Step Function pipelines on a fixed cadence, and an
      autonomous feedback loop that writes optimized parameters back into the
      system.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      The harness is the durable artifact; alpha capture against the S&amp;P 500
      is the first experiment inside it. The system is currently in
      <strong class="text-zinc-100">Phase 2: Reliability + Measurability buildout</strong>
      &mdash; making the instrument trustworthy enough that Phase 3 can turn alpha
      tuning on. Alpha is tracked, but not optimized, until measurement is
      trustworthy.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">Origin</h2>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      <strong class="text-zinc-100">Nous Ergon</strong> &mdash; Greek for <em>intelligence at work</em>
      (&nu;&omicron;&upsilon;&sigmaf; &epsilon;&rho;&gamma;&omicron;&nu;,
      pronounced <em>noose air-gone</em>).
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      <em>Nous</em> (&nu;&omicron;&upsilon;&sigmaf;) is mind, intellect, the capacity for reason.
      <em>Ergon</em> (&epsilon;&rho;&gamma;&omicron;&nu;) is work, deed, function &mdash; the same root as
      English <em>ergonomics</em> and <em>energy</em>. The name frames what the project is:
      agentic intelligence applied to a measurable, continuously verifiable problem.
      The work &mdash; the <em>ergon</em> &mdash; is what's on display.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">Built by</h2>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      <strong class="text-zinc-100">Brian McMahon.</strong> Single-developer project,
      in development since March 2026; <strong class="text-zinc-100">Claude Code</strong>
      (Anthropic's LLM coding assistant) is the active collaborator on the
      implementation pass. Each module's repo is public.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Nous Ergon is a harness for agentic-orchestration research where different
      architectures, models, and patterns can be tested against measured
      baselines. Equities were chosen because financial data is abundant,
      decisions are unambiguous, and outcomes are continuously verifiable.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      The system is also a demonstration of how AI-augmented solo engineering can scale.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">Contact</h2>
    <ul class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 space-y-1">
      <li><a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/brian-c-mcmahon/">LinkedIn</a></li>
      <li><a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="mailto:brian@nousergon.ai">brian@nousergon.ai</a></li>
      <li><a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="https://github.com/cipher813">GitHub</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>
